{"displayTopicName":"Identifying verbs","topicTokens":[{"text":"Identifying verbs","type":"text"}],"paragraphsBySubtopic":{"2":[{"text":"Every Hebrew and Aramaic verb comes from a shoresh or root.\nA root is a short series of letters that produces a family of related words. For example: \n","type":"text"},{"type":"table","rows":[[{"tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Shoresh","type":"text"}]}]},{"tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":" Meaning","type":"text"}]}]}],[{"tokens":[{"text":"אכל","type":"text"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"Eating","type":"text"}]}],[{"tokens":[{"text":"הלך","type":"text"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"Walking / travel","type":"text"}]}],[{"tokens":[{"text":"אמר","type":"text"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"Speech","type":"text"}]}]]},{"text":"\nWe identify the root of a word by finding which letters are not part of suffixes or prefixes.\nLooking at our word מאכיל, we can identify the shoresh אכל, which is used to produce words related to the concept of “eating.”\n","type":"text"},{"type":"menu","alignment":"right","rtl":false,"items":[{"list":false,"hidden":false,"tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"local","tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"text"}],"targetSubtopic":"3","targetTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"2"}]}]}],"3":[{"text":"Every Hebrew and Aramaic verb has what’s called a “binyan.”\nA binyan is a theme of meaning that is combined with a shoresh to produce a verb family.\nFor example, you might have a binyan whose theme is “causative,” i.e. it produces verbs where an actor causes another thing to do a given action.\nPutting the shoresh אכל into a “causative” binyan might produce the verb לְהָכִיל, ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"lehachil","type":"text"}]},{"text":", “to feed” (i.e, to ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"cause","type":"text"}]},{"text":" someone else to eat.)\nEvery binyan has a special pattern of spelling and pronunciation that allows us to identify words in that binyan.\nThis is a diagram of all the binyanim:\n","type":"text"},{"type":"table","rows":[[{"tokens":[{"text":"*Hebrew*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Hebrew","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Hebrew_binyanim","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"*Simple*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Simple","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Simple","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"*Intensive*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Intensive","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Intensive","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"*Causative*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Causative","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Causative","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"*Reflexive*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Reflexive","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Reflexive","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]}],[{"tokens":[{"text":"*Active*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Active","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Active","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Pa’al_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Pa’al","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Pa’al","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Pi’el_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Pi’el","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Pi’el","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Hif’il_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Hif’il","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Hif’il","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Hispa’el_\\,<br>_Nispa’el_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Hispa’el","type":"text"}]},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<br>"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Nispa’el","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Hispa’el,_Nispa’el","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}],"rowspan":2}],[{"tokens":[{"text":"*Passive*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Passive","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Passive","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Nif’al_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Nif’al","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Nif’al","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Pu’al_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Pu’al","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Pu’al","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Huf’al_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Huf’al","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Huf’al","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[],"merge":true}]]},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<meta>"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"table","rows":[[{"tokens":[{"text":"*Aramaic*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Aramaic","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Aramaic_binyanim","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"*Simple*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Simple","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Simple","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"*Intensive*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Intensive","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Intensive","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"*Causative*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Causative","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Causative","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]}],[{"tokens":[{"text":"*Active*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Active","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Active","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Pe’al_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Pe’al","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Pe’al","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Pa’el_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Pa’el","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Pa’el","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Af’el_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Af’el","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Af’el","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]}],[{"tokens":[{"text":"*Passive*","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Passive","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Aramaic_Passive_%2F_Reflexive","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Ispe’el_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Ispe’el","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Ispe’el","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Ispa’al_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Ispa’al","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Ispa’al","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"_Itaf’al_","type":"global","tokens":[{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"Itaf’al","type":"text"}]}],"pathString":"Itaf’al","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]}]]},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"menu","alignment":"right","rtl":false,"items":[{"list":false,"hidden":false,"tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"local","tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"text"}],"targetSubtopic":"4","targetTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"3"}]}]}],"4":[{"text":"Every verb has what’s called a “tense.”\nFor example, taking our verb מאכיל, we might know that the spelling indicates a verb that describes a habitual or ongoing action e.g. “he feeds” or “he is feeding,” as opposed to e.g. “he fed” or “will feed.” (The technical term for this tense is the “active participle.”)\nThis is a diagram of all the tenses:\n","type":"text"},{"type":"table","rows":[[{"tokens":[{"text":"Past Tense","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"Past Tense","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Past_tense","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"4"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"Future Tense","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"Future Tense","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Future_Tense","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"4"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"Active Participle","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"Active Participle","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Active_Participle","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"4"}]}],[{"tokens":[{"text":"Imperative","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"Imperative","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Imperative","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"4"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"Infinitive","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"Infinitive","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Infinitive","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"4"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"Passive Participle","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"Passive Participle","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Passive_Participle","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"4"}]}]]},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"menu","alignment":"right","rtl":false,"items":[{"list":false,"hidden":false,"tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"local","tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"text"}],"targetSubtopic":"5","targetTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"4"}]}]}],"5":[{"text":"Every verb has a “conjugation,” additional information about who is doing the action.\nConjugation always includes what are called “gender” and “number.” This tells you how many people are doing the action, and whether they are masculine or feminine.\nSome verbs also include “person” e.g. whether I am doing it, you are doing it, he is doing it, etc. Our example of מאכיל is masculine singular, indicating a single male doer, and does not have “person” information.\n","type":"text"},{"type":"menu","alignment":"right","rtl":false,"items":[{"list":false,"hidden":false,"tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"local","tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"text"}],"targetSubtopic":"6","targetTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"5"}]}]}],"6":[{"text":"For every combination of a binyan and a tense, there will be a table of conjugations for every person. For example, these are the conjugations for the “hif’il active participle” which מַאֲכִיל belongs to:\n","type":"text"},{"type":"table","rows":[[{"tokens":[],"hidden":true},{"tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Masculine","type":"text"}]}]},{"tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Feminine","type":"text"}]}]}],[{"tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Singular","type":"text"}]}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"מַבְדִּיל ","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<br><br>"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"mavdil","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<br><br><br>"},{"text":" [he is] separating","type":"text"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"מַבְדִּילָה ","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<br><br>"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"mavdilau","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<br><br><br>"},{"text":" [she is] separating","type":"text"}]}],[{"tokens":[{"type":"bold","tokens":[{"text":"Plural","type":"text"}]}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"מַבְדִּילִים ","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<br><br>"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"mavdilim","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<br><br><br>"},{"text":" [those men are] separating","type":"text"}]},{"tokens":[{"text":"מַבְדִּילוֹת ","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<br><br>"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"italics","tokens":[{"text":"mavdilos","type":"text"}]},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"html_element","tokenInsertions":[],"html":"<br><br><br>"},{"text":" [those women are] separating","type":"text"}]}]]},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"menu","alignment":"right","rtl":false,"items":[{"list":false,"hidden":false,"tokens":[{"text":"Got it","type":"global","tokens":[{"text":"Got it","type":"text"}],"pathString":"Identifying_verbs#Identifying_verbs","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"6"}]}]}],"Identifying verbs":[{"text":"Identifying a verb in Hebrew or Aramaic entails identifying several important pieces of information about the word. For example, let’s identify the verb “מאכיל.”\n","type":"text"},{"type":"menu","alignment":"right","rtl":false,"items":[{"list":false,"hidden":false,"tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"local","tokens":[{"text":"Okay","type":"text"}],"targetSubtopic":"2","targetTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingTopic":"Identifying verbs","enclosingSubtopic":"Identifying verbs"}]}]}]}}